# Help
# ============================================================================
show_root_help() {
    cat <<EOF
mlx — manage local MLX inference servers

USAGE
    mlx <command> [flags]

LIFECYCLE COMMANDS
    start       Start chat, tags, embed, tts, and kokoro servers
    stop        Stop running servers (chat, tags, embed, tts, kokoro, or all)
    restart     Stop, then start (use --chat-model NAME to swap profiles)
    status      Show running servers, PIDs, and registered chat profiles

DIAGNOSTICS
    monitor     Poll per-server RSS over time (catch cache growth)
    tail        Follow a server's log (chat, tags, embed, tts, kokoro)
    config      Print resolved configuration (incl. registered profiles)

DIRECT INFERENCE  (one-shot prompts to a running server)
    chat        Send a prompt to the chat server (port ${CHAT_PORT}); streams to stdout
    tags        Send a prompt to the tags server (port ${TAGS_PORT}); streams to stdout
    tag         Send an image to the tags server and get positive + negative tags

PROXY
    router      OpenAI-compatible proxy fronting chat (swap-on-demand) plus
                static tags/embed/tts backends. See "mlx router help".

OTHER
    help        Help for any command (start, stop, restart, status, monitor,
                tail, config, chat, tags, tag, embed, tts, kokoro, router)

FLAGS
    -h, --help  Show this help

Run "mlx <command> --help" for command-specific help.

CHAT MODEL PROFILES
    Multiple chat models can be registered as profiles in mlx.conf.
    Switch with: mlx restart chat --chat-model NAME
    See registered profiles with: mlx config

    Each profile can carry three things in mlx.conf:
      CHAT_MODEL_PROFILES[name]    model path (required)
      CHAT_DRAFT_PROFILES[name]    spec-dec draft path ("" disables)
      CHAT_ENGINE_PROFILES[name]   "lm" (text, default) or "vlm" (multimodal)
    Set engine = vlm for image-capable models (Llama-4 Scout, etc.) so the
    chat server boots mlx_vlm.server and accepts image_url content blocks.

CONFIGURATION
    Edit ~/.config/mlx.conf to change models, ports, cache sizes,
    spec-dec settings, profile registry, per-profile engine, etc.
    Run "mlx config" to see resolved values.

    Override precedence (highest wins): command flags > env vars > config
    file > built-in defaults.

    Override the config file path with MLX_CONFIG_FILE env var.
EOF
}

